solution: ```class SeatManager {
    private final PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap;

    public SeatManager(int n) {
        minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>(n);
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            minHeap.offer(i);
        }
    }

    public int reserve() {
        return minHeap.poll();
    }

    public void unreserve(int seatNumber) {
        minHeap.offer(seatNumber);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n) for both reserve and unreserve
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a min-heap to always return the smallest available seat in O(log n) time. Initialization pre-loads all seats into the heap. Unreserve simply re-inserts the seat into the heap.

